Link to 6 month article<a class="" href="">?</a></p>


<h2 class="dontend" id="toc0"> Questions <a href="#toc0"> <sup><i class="fa fa-link invert" ></i></sup> </a></h2>
<ul class="ulbasic">
    <li class="libasic">We are building a business process, 1 meeting at a time. Pls input in the relevant gaps...</li>
    <li class="libasic">Is the velocity high enough? </li>
    <li class="libasic">Are you happy with current process?</li>
</ul>


<h2 class="dontend" id="toc1"> Planned deliverables  <a href="#toc1"> <sup><i class="fa fa-link invert" ></i></sup> </a></h2>
<ul class="ulbasic">
    <li class="libasic">I am removing RappidJS<a class="" href="https://www.google.co.uk/search?q=RappidJS">?</a> (which makes SVG) to just make SVG directly. Value to business: plain SVG is scaling to active screen size AND as I have direct control, I can fix all the stupid layout issues. </li>
    <li class="libasic">Recent work focussing on RWD improves usefulness of tool. Business value: its what one of you or sales directly asked for.</li>
    <li class="libasic">I think we should think about fonts <sup><a href="https://blog.kurtosys.com/fonts-for-finance-typefaces-best/" target="_blank">1</a></sup> <sup><a href="https://www.typography.com/techniques/fonts-for-financials/" target="_blank">2</a></sup> <sup><a href="http://typ.io/tags/finance" target="_blank">3</a></sup>. I suggest <sup><a href="http://freakfonts.com/fonts/interstate-regular-font-download.html" target="_blank">4</a></sup>, but will think more...</li>
    <li class="libasic">Unrushing code, mostly done in the last few months; so anything after point is cheaper. Business value: so everything you want in the future is simple/cheap.</li>
    <li class="libasic">Documentation of the webstack, RS says he needs it.</li>
    <li class="libasic"></li>
</ul>


